Parliament, Tuesday 15 October 2019 – Three young Members of Parliament (MPs), who are all under 35 years, will be participating in the youth indaba of the Southern African Development Community Parliamentary Forum (SADC-PF) to be held in Pretoria from 15 to 17 October 2019. The three MPs - Mr Xola Nqola, Ms Nazley Sharif (both from the National Assembly) and Mr Itumeleng Ntsube (from the National Council of Provinces) – will be attending the indaba whose focus is: “Youth-led accountability within the national Parliaments – towards delivering on sexual and reproductive health and rights, HIV and gender equality political commitments in the SADC region.” The objective of the Indaba is to support the ongoing celebration of the 25th anniversary of the International Conference on Population and Development as well as the SADC-PF’s policy commitment to promote youth participation in SADC’s political and economic governance. The third day, 17 October, of the Indaba will be an intergenerational parliamentary dialogue which will allow MPs of all ages and youth activists to share their views and perspectives on the theme. DETAILS ARE AS FOLLOWS: Date: Tuesday, 15 to 17 October 2019
	Time: 08h30 till 17h00
	Venue: Protea Hotel (by Marriot), 1141 Burnett Street, Hatfield, Pretoria For media enquiries or requests for interviews with the delegation please contact: Modise Kabeli
	Cell: 081 715 9969
	Email: mkabeli@parliament.gov.za ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENT OF THE REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA
